x4freetext: USED TO PRODUCE A COLLIMATED 170 KEV DEUTERON BEAM.
A 2.4 CI (3-H)-TI-CU TARGET WAS USED TO
THE MULTIPARAMETER DATA FROM THE EIGHT DETEC-
TORS IN THE TWO TELESCOPES WERE ANALYSED IN REAL TIME
FOR PARTICLE IDENTIFICATION, AND THE ENERGY SPECTRA
OF THE SEPARATED CHARGED PARTICLES WERE OBTAINED IN
PLACED 4.6 CM FROM THE LITHIUM TARGET, WERE USED EACH
CONSISTING OF TWO GAS PROPORTIONAL COUNTERS, ONE
DELTA-E AND ONE E SILICON SURFACE BARRIER DETECTOR.
IN ONE TELESCOPE THE SILICON DETECTORS WERE OF 32 AND
1500 MICRONS RESPECTIVELY, IN THE OTHER 16 AND 1500
MICRONS. A 5 MM DIAM COLLIMATOR WAS PLACED IN FRONT
A NE213 LIQUID SCINTILLATOR AND A SI P-I-N
PHOTODIODE PLACED 100 CM AND 3 CM RESPECTIVELY FROM
TH NEUTRON SOURCE POINT AND AT 0 DEG AND 90 DEG
RESPECTIVELY TO THE DEUTERON BEAM WERE USED AS
.ANOTHER SI P-I-N PHOTODIODE WAS USED TO DETERMINE THE
NEUTRON YIELD OF THE TRITIUM TARGET BY THE ASSOCIATED
WAS PREPARED BY ROLLING AND PLACED ON THE UPPER HOLE
OF AN AL OR TA HOLDER WHICH HAD TWO HOLES OF 5.9 MM
DIAM. THIS SAMPLE WAS PLACED 3.0 CM FROM THE NEUTRON
PRODUCING TARGET AT THE CENTRE OF A SCATTERING
